node.text: Do you get what I’m saying babes? I always just assumed that when a relationship ended everything would be split down the middle and be FAIR 🤷🏻‍♀️ I’m a little shocked that it’s just not the case. I have friends who are supporting their families without any contribution from their ex (usually both financially and emotionally) and can’t afford to get legal advice or get no help from government in pursuing what they should be receiving from the dad. I feel that as a woman it makes us feel particularly vulnerable and unheard, unseen and under recognized for what we have to do. I’m just a little stunned that it’s still happening, that a woman’s worth as a mother, provider and carer is still not valued. I’ve had to deal with my own situation and anger around it (and honestly I’ll be ok - I have a roof over my head at least) but I know so many women trying to keep it together and support their family who aren’t as lucky as me. What do you think? Has this been your experience too? Something needs to change 🤔🙃🙌🏽 #metoo #divorce #relationships #parenting #feminism #support #mama #menopausemademedoit #thegoddesschronicles #middleagedgoddess

This really struck a nerve, you hit the nail on the head...I was a single mom on welfare in my mid 30s, forced into bankruptcy when my ex's creditors came after me once he filed, he did a brilliant job of hiding his income or switching jobs so there was never a way to collect on child support...interestingly when I look back I can see the gifts in all the contrast and hardships, I forged a new stronger self during that time, rebuilt my credit over time, enough to start my own design biz,  bought a car & house in my own name, started another biz in my 50s that grew multimillion $ in annual revenue, and in an wonderful twist was able to retire my 2nd hub & life partner...

@art_of_healthy_aging all this to say, the moment I let go of my victim status, was the moment I found out how strong I really was...when I didn't have a choice, I had to figure it out... when  I finally  realized there was no one coming to the rescue , when I surendered all my anger, frustration & bitterness & resentment that was eating me up & keeping me small,  was moment started to make my way back to a joy filled life...it took me a decade to build that mindset but it opened me up to the creative solutions that helped empower me and own my life ❤️💕 my heart goes out to every woman that has to go through  this, it should never be like this if we were dealing with a level playing field 💕 but we can rise above it, we can be our own champions 💃🎉 this I know 😘

@art_of_healthy_aging wow! And I know so many women like you who have gathered their strength and gone ok I need to do this and have quietly (or loudly) made their own success.  I also know women who are crumbling under the stress of managing kids (some with disabilities), work, mortgage repayments AND menopause! But we do it don’t we? I am continually astounded at the strength of women and you’re one of them 🙌🏽🙌🏽🙌🏽
